pwd : current path 
sudo useradd -m username : add user

ls  -la : list all  
cat /etc/passwd : list all users 

cd ~   : your home directory 
cd /     : root level

sudo passwd username : set username’s password

su – username : switch user to username
sudo –i : switch to root

wsl --user root : on powershell if you want to reset passwords you can login as root
whoami : current user

wsl --list –verbose : list  linux instances running on wsl 

man command :  manual entry (documentation) on “command” 

finger :  list users that are logged in 

sudo apt install : install commands 

















  
